Task name: Research and write a detailed report about JAVA (history, uses, advantages, disadvantages, etc.).
1.Introduction
Java is a high-level, object-oriented programming language developed by Sun Microsystems in 1995. It is designed to be platform-independent, meaning programs written in Java can run on any system that has a Java Virtual Machine (JVM)________________________________________
2. History of Java
•	Java was developed by James Gosling and his team at Sun Microsystems. 
•	Initially called Oak, it was later renamed Java. 
•	Released officially in 1995. 
•	Acquired by Oracle Corporation in 2010. 
•	Popular due to its “Write Once, Run Anywhere (WORA)” capability. 
________________________________________
3. Features of Java
•	Platform Independent – Runs on any OS via JVM 
•	Object-Oriented – Uses classes and objects 
•	Simple & Easy to Learn 
•	Secure – No direct memory access 
•	Robust – Strong memory management 
•	Multithreaded – Can perform multiple tasks simultaneously 
•	Distributed – Supports network-based applications________________________________________

4. Uses of Java
Java is widely used in many fields:
•	Web Development (Spring, JSP, Servlets) 
•	Mobile Applications (Android apps) 
•	Desktop Applications 
•	Enterprise Applications (banking systems, ERP) 
•	Game Development 
•	Cloud-based Applications 
•	Big Data Technologies (Hadoop) ________________________________________
5. Advantages of Java
•	Platform independent 
•	Large community support 
•	High security 
•	Rich API (Application Programming Interface) 
•	Automatic garbage collection 
•	Scalable and reliable 
6. Disadvantages of Java
•	Slower than low-level languages like C/C++ 
•	Requires more memory 
•	Verbose (more lines of code) 
•	GUI development is less attractive compared to modern frameworks 
•	Performance overhead due to JVM 
7. Conclusion
Java remains one of the most popular programming languages due to its reliability, security, and cross-platform capabilities. It is widely used in industry and continues to evolve with new technologies.
